By Nse Anthony-Uko
(Sundiata Post) — Students of Department of Criminology, University of Ilorin, Nigeria were asked to answer questions on the issues of Evans the Kidnapper, the Snake that swallowed N36 million in JAMB Office as well has Jacob Zuma’s resignation as president of South Africa in their Semester Examination. In a Course titled ‘Interrogation, Confession and Testimony’, in the Department of Criminology and Security Studies, the students were given five questions to answer and the first question which was compulsory was on Zuma’s resignation.
View below the Question Paper that has since gone viral. 